cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to predict the next participant in a multi-party conversation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and Maximum Likelihood Expectation (MLE) which are common techniques in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with dialogue errors and simulating user interaction, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed architecture in improving human-computer interaction, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
